<content>
<![CDATA[
<p>Small-business apps make it easy for small-business owners to manage and run their businesses from their smartphones or tablets. Whether you're looking for an application to help you stay productive while youre on the go or to help you back up data, it's easy to find one that suits your needs. Once youve started using some of the top business applications, youll wonder how you managed without them in the past.</p>

<p>
<strong>Benefits of Small-Business Apps</strong></p>

<p>You will find numerous benefits to using 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/Tablets/cat_CL204449">small-business apps</a> to manage your business. Not only do applications allow you to access your company's data remotely, but they also help you to keep working when you aren't at the office. Some of the top small-business apps allow you to:</p>

<p> Create, edit, and view documents</p>

<p> Back up important information</p>

<p> View PDF files</p>

<p> Chat with employees</p>

<p> Monitor your business operations</p>

<p> Track and analyze data</p>

<p>
<strong>Types of Technology Available </strong></p>

<p>Whether youre interested in backing up data or working remotely, plenty of small-business apps are available. It's important to consider what you need to accomplish when you choose which apps you want to use for your business. Some of the top small-business apps include:</p>

<p> Google Drive</p>

<p> Microsoft SkyDrive</p>

<p> Adobe PDF File Viewer</p>

<p> OfficeTime</p>

<p> Polaris Office</p>

<p>Google Drive and Microsoft SkyDrive are ideal choices for business owners who are 
<a href="https://appcenter.staples.com/apps/3952?1708913328">backing up data</a> and important documents. Internet-based storage applications give you ample room to store files, and you can access them from any location.</p>

