<p>
<strong>The Cost of Using Small-Business Apps</strong></p>

<p>The cost of using small-business apps depends on the type of application you choose to use. For example, if you want Google Drive to back up data, you can use the app for free. However, applications like OfficeTime and Polaris Office can cost anywhere from $15 to $70. The more advanced the application is, the more it will cost you, but you need to keep in mind that this is typically a once-only fee, and the amount of time small-business apps can save employees could end up saving you a lot of money in the long run.</p>

<p>Staying productive when you arent at your office and backing up your companys data doesn't have to be difficult. Small-business apps can help you accomplish a variety of tasks and keep you on top of anything related to your business. Small-business apps make running your business simple, and once you begin to use the apps, you won't know how to function without them.</p>
