<title>5 Cutting-Edge Mobile App Development Tools</title>
<description>Choosing the right app development tools is a key part of expanding your business's online presence.</description>
<link>http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/tech-articles/5-cutting-edge-mobile-app-development-tools.html</link>
<media:thumbnail url="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/images/res/5-cutting-edge-mobile-app_sbba_b11_0011.jpg"></media:thumbnail>
<pubDate>28 Mar 2013 13:11:08 GMT</pubDate>
<content>
<![CDATA[
<p>To keep your business accessible to the growing segment of your customer base that uses smartphones, you may want to create a mobile app. The kind of app you will need depends on the nature of your business  restaurants should consider menu apps, while retail stores may want a mobile shopping app. Choosing the right app development tools is an important part of expanding your business's online presence. When budgeting for creation of a mobile app, remember that it is only part of your electronic presence and for most businesses, it will not replace an attractive and functional website.</p>

<p>
<strong>Apples Xcode</strong></p>

<p>Apples Xcode is free to download and use, so it is one of the most economical 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/tech-articles/identify-acquire-and-master-the-technology-that-will-drive-your-small-business.html">mobile app development tools</a>. It is widely used throughout the Mac development community and is often the preferred choice for integrated development environments (IDEs). It includes an iOS simulator and a wide range of software development kits (SDKs) and Cocoa frameworks for both desktop and mobile devices. Its intuitive interface is well-organized and integrated for editing, debugging and compiling your code.</p>

<p>
<strong>Google ADT (Android Development Tools) </strong></p>

<p>Develop your Android application using Googles ADT. This plug-in will allow you to build your Android app with ease by harnessing the Android Framework API and SDK tools in one simple interface, making it a one-stop option to help you make a mobile app.</p>

<p>Appcelerators Titanium</p>

<p>This mobile app development tool helps you develop code for virtually any device. Write your code once, and compile it for Googles Android and Apples iPhone or iPad. Using the Eclipse IDE interface, you can write your code in one universal language, Javascript, and leverage Eclipses massive collection of device and mobile APIs.</p>

<p>
<strong>appMobi jqMobi </strong></p>

<p>If you're looking for 
<a href="www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/tech-articles/10-tips-for-mobile-device-management.html">app development tools</a> that are lightweight and use cutting-edge technology, appMobi jqMobi is a solid choice. jQuery and HTML5 are popular, but jqMobi was created specifically for mobile devices, and its open-source, making it one of the more economic app development tools around. jqUI allows you to develop your app for Googles Android and Apples iPhone and iPad with ease.</p>

<p>
<strong>MobileFrame</strong></p>

<p>Mobile Frame can help you create a mobile app for your business, even if you don't have programming skills. It boasts a WYSIWYG interface and is packed with pre-built functions, so you can design an app just by clicking. Support for HTML5 and a wide array of popular features make MobileFrame one of the app development tools of choice for many business owners.</p>

<p>
<strong>Professional Assistance</strong></p>

<p>If you don't have the time or technical skill to create an app that meets your needs, you might consider hiring a professional developer to create an app for your business. You can find boutique developers to create high-end, visually stunning apps, as well as economical developers who will create simple and functional apps.</p>

<p>When creating a mobile app for your business, you can take advantage of many different app development tools at varying price points. Mobile app development tools offer different functions and are compatible with a range of systems, so consider your customers' needs when choosing. Whether you create an app on your own or hire a professional developer, the important thing is that it is accessible to your customers, easy to use and represents your company's image.</p>
]]></content></item>
<item>
<title>Six Dimensions: Understanding Social Media Literacy for Business Leaders</title>
<description>Social media has several business-boosting benefits.</description>
<link>http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/tech-articles/six-dimensions-understanding-social-media-literacy-for-business-leaders.html</link>
<media:thumbnail url="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/images/res/6-dimensions-understanding-social-media_sbba_b11_0006.jpg"></media:thumbnail>
<pubDate>28 Mar 2013 13:01:56 GMT</pubDate>
<content>
<![CDATA[
<p>Social media tools make it easy for small business owners to interact with their current customers while attracting new clients, too. As a result, understanding social media is essential for small businesses that rely on Facebook and Twitter to get the word out about their company.</p>

<p>
<strong>The Benefits of Social Media</strong></p>

<p>Social media has several business-boosting benefits. First, it helps level the playing field between small businesses and the large organizations that use powerful marketing and public relations strategies. Social media make it possible for any business owner with a computer to let people know about new products and services, upcoming events and other information that might appeal to potential customers. Understanding social media also makes it possible for small business owners to generate excitement about their companies. Small businesses typically can't afford full-page magazine ads or 30-second TV spots. However, social media makes it possible for them to get their message out to thousands of people at very little cost. Ultimately, this type of marketing can help drive Web site traffic, locate potential customers and create a consistent brand image across several platforms.</p>

<p>As a business owner, you should be familiar with the six dimensions of social media marketing literacy:</p>

<p>1) At the personal level, you should be able to understand what makes social media messages go viral.</p>

<p>2) As a social media producer, you should develop an authentic voice and be able to create compelling content.</p>

<p>3) As a recipient of social media messages, you should be able to filter through messages to find the ones that are most important.</p>

<p>4) At the organizational level, you should be able to coordinate social media activities and support an interactive social media environment.</p>

<p>5) As an advisor, you should understand the cultural impact of social media and leverage its power for marketing and other business functions.</p>

<p>6) At an analytical level, you should be able to monitor and respond to social trends as they are happening.</p>

<p>
<strong>Technology &amp;amp; Innovations to Help You Understand Social Media</strong></p>

<p>Those interested in 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/Mobile-Phones/cat_DP5128">understanding social media</a> realize that anyone with a computer or mobile phone can connect with customers and spread the word about a company's products and services. In the past, business owners had to spend a lot of time and money buying advertising, working with public relations consultants and making pitches to reporters. With social media, however, small business owners can reach their target audience directly and eliminate those costs. Improving your understanding of social media can help you drive sales, increase customer satisfaction and streamline your marketing efforts.</p>

<p>
<strong>The Cost of Keeping Up </strong></p>

<p>Along with giving you direct access to your customers, another benefit of social media is that its extremely cost effective. In fact, many social media tools are free. You may have to buy some social media apps for your laptop, tablet or mobile device, but the cost is minimal  only a few dollars for each application. The low cost of these apps makes increasing your 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/All-Laptop-Computers/cat_CL167289">social media literacy</a> an easy way to reduce your marketing expenses. There are a few social media pitfalls your business should avoid. One major mistake is using social media to argue with customers who have complained about your products or services. Another is posting too many messages that aren't relevant to people in your target market. Be careful to post targeted messages that will appeal to the people you want to have as customers.</p>

<p>Social media is an important part of your marketing strategy, as it helps you reach a broad audience without significantly increasing your costs. Make sure you invest in the right tools and educational products that will help you understand how to use social media properly.</p>
]]></content></item>
