<title>The Best Mobile Apps for Small-Business Warriors</title>
<description>Mobile apps make business travel less stressful. We gathered some of the best apps for life on the road. Upload these apps to make life on the road a little bit easier.</description>
<link>http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/easytech-u/small-business-road-warrior-101/the-best-mobile-apps-for-small-business-warriors.html</link>
<media:thumbnail url="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/images/res/road-warrior-2-335.jpg"></media:thumbnail>
<pubDate>07 Aug 2012 18:29:43 GMT</pubDate>
<content>
<![CDATA[
<blockquote>
<p>Mobile apps make business travel less stressful. We gathered some of the best apps for life on the road. Upload these apps to make life on the road a little bit easier.</p></blockquote>

<p>Mobile apps can make life easier for small-business road warriors. Whether you need to take notes, connect your notebook to the Internet, or call a cab on short notice, these apps will make your time on the road more productive and less stressful.</p>

<ul>

<li>
<strong>Dropbox</strong>: In addition to notebooks, you can send and download files from your phone with Dropboxs free app.</li>

<li>
<strong>Evernote</strong>: a note-taking mobile app, Evernote also allows you to record voice notes. In addition, Evernote lets you record expense receipts and business cards with your cameras phone.</li>

<li>
<strong>Livo Recorder Pro</strong>: This voice-recording app allows you to record memos, lectures, and notes. You can email voice recordings or add them to Dropbox.</li>

<li>
<strong>PdaNet</strong>:
<strong> </strong>One of several tethering apps, PdaNet allows you to hook your notebook up to your phone and access the Internet through your mobile plan. If your phone plan doesnt offer tethering, this little app solves the problem nicely.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>Taxi Magic</strong>: Possibly the most useful apps on this list, Taxi magic locates, books, and tracks nearby cabs in over 40 U.S. cities. You can even pay the fare through your phone.</p>
]]></content></item>
<item>
<title>Small Business Road Warrior Travel Bag Checklist</title>
<description>Wondering what to pack for that business trip? Check out our list of essential gadgets for the small-business road warrior. Youll want to make sure youve got all the tools for life on the road.</description>
<link>http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/easytech-u/small-business-road-warrior-101/small-business-road-warrior-travel-bag-checklist.html</link>
<media:thumbnail url="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/images/res/road-warrior335.jpg"></media:thumbnail>
<pubDate>07 Aug 2012 18:26:40 GMT</pubDate>
<content>
<![CDATA[
<blockquote>
<p>Wondering what to pack for that business trip? Check out our list of essential gadgets for the small-business road warrior. Youll want to make sure youve got all the tools for life on the road.</p></blockquote>

<p>Every small-business road warrior has a set of gadgets that he or she relies on, developed over years of travel. If you lack the experience of the seasoned road warrior, dont fret. Weve created a quick list of essential gear, gadgets, and tools that every traveling small-business owner should have in their carry-on or glove box. If youre heading out on a road trip, take these essentials with you:</p>

<ul>

<li>
<strong>Car charger:</strong> keep your devices charged while you drive.</li>

<li>
<strong>Noise-reducing headset:</strong> block out airplane engines, screaming kids, and other travel noise.</li>

<li>
<strong>Notebook lock:</strong> a lock and cable antitheft system reduces the risk of returning to your hotel room to discover your notebook left without you.</li>

<li>
<strong>Pocket projector:</strong> for wowing clients with instant presentations.</li>

<li>
<strong>Portable mouse:</strong> for those times when you actually can work at a desk.</li>

<li>
<strong>Portable battery pack:</strong> a universal travel battery recharges your devices when you cant plug in.</li>

<li>
<strong>Single-to-triple AC adapter:</strong> because there are never enough wall outlets in a hotel room.</li>

<li>
<strong>USB AC adapter:</strong> turn any outlet into a USB charger.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>USB Pocket Hard Drive:</strong> for easily transferring files from your notebook to other computers.</p>
]]></content></item>
<item>
<title>Top Tech Tips for the Small-Business Road Warrior</title>
<description>The small-business road warrior stays productive in and out of the office. Learn the tricks veteran business travelers use to travel light without sacrificing work cycles. Follow these tips and youll be a road warrior in no time.</description>
<link>http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/explore-tips-and-advice/easytech-u/small-business-road-warrior-101/top-tech-tips-for-the-small-business-road-warrior.html</link>
<media:thumbnail url="http://www.staples.com/sbd/cre/tech-services/images/res/road-warrior-1-335.jpg"></media:thumbnail>
<pubDate>07 Aug 2012 18:21:48 GMT</pubDate>
<content>
<![CDATA[
<blockquote>
<p>The small-business road warrior stays productive in and out of the office. Learn the tricks veteran business travelers use to travel light without sacrificing work cycles. Follow these tips and youll be a road warrior in no time.</p></blockquote>

<p>Many small-business owners find themselves working from airport departure lobbies as often as they work at the home office. If this describes you, or if youre gearing up for a one-time business trip, our experts can help you travel like a true small-business road warrior.</p>

<h2>Laptop, Notebook, or Tablet?</h2>

<p>Gone are the days when road warriors lugged 17-inch laptops through airport security checkpoints. Replace that 6-lb. monster with a smaller notebook that only weighs 4 lbs. and fits easily on an airplane food tray (
<a href="http://www.staples.com/Ultrabooks-PCs-Laptops-Tablets/cat_CL166724">ultrabooks</a> are a good start).</p>

<p>You can lighten the load even further by switching to a 1.5-lb. tablet that also doubles as an 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/E-Readers-E-Readers-Accessories/cat_CL164364">ereader</a>, removing the need to travel with both a laptop and Kindle. A tablets recharging cord has the extra benefit of being lighter and easier to pack than a notebook power cord.</p>

<h2>Doodads and Gadgets</h2>

<p>Any road warrior worth the name has a list of gadgets to increase business productivity. Multipurpose gadgets such as pocket projectors that double as camcorders and digital cameras are special favorites, as such devices cut down on packing. Other popular choices include:</p>

<ul>

<li>Business-card readers</li>

<li>Combination wall socket/car charger to keep devices powered</li>

<li>Mini power strips to maximize hotel wall sockets</li>

<li>Portable wireless speakers for presentations</li>

<li>
<a href="http://www.staples.com/USB-Cables-Power-Cables-Adapters-Chargers/cat_CL140709">Retractable USB cables</a>, for easy packing</li>
</ul>

<h2>Bagging it All Up</h2>

<p>A skilled road warrior doesnt skimp on a 
<a href="http://www.staples.com/Laptop-Bags-Luggage-PCs-Drives-Accessories/cat_CG20">travel bag</a>. The right bag is made of durable, lightweight material and contains plenty of pockets and dividers for easy organization.</p>

<p>Shop for a travel bag with Transport Security Administration guidelines in mind. Youll want a bag that is checkpoint permissible, or your entire road warrior kit could wind up travelling in the cargo hold.</p>

<p>If a bags shoulder strap makes carrying it uncomfortable, you can buy ergonomic replacement shoulder straps online. Travel produces enough stress without adding a sore shoulder to the equation.</p>

<p>Power cords and device chargers can get overlooked in the flurry of packing that precedes a business trip. To prevent this, buy a second set of chargers that lives in your travel bag. That way, theyre all packed and ready for you.</p>

<h2>Road Trip Survival Tips</h2>

<p>Before you depart, make sure you charge every device you take with you so you can get the maximum use out of your electronics. Some road warriors keep packing and pre-travel checklists on their smartphones for easy access.</p>

<p>Prepacking duplicate chargers has already been mentioned. If you travel regularly, consider prepacking other essentials; toiletries, underwear, socks, and stationery can all be packed in advance.</p>

<p>Business travel often means transporting sensitive corporate information. Instead of transporting such information on easily stolen notebooks, phones, or USB flash drives, you can store files in the cloud through services such as Dropboxthus keeping transported data to a minimum.</p>

<p>Finally, consider purchasing a prepaid phone card for landline use. Hotels charge exorbitant rates for phone use; you cant always rely on cell phone service and cellphones are a popular target for thieves. A prepaid card saves you money if you ever have to contact the home office in an emergency.</p>

<p>Follow these tips before you head out to the open road, and youll be able to conduct business from anywhere.</p>
]]></content></item>
