<blockquote>
<p>Which cloud services are ideal for small businesses? Its hard to say, but certain traits do lend themselves well to the cloud. What are they?</p></blockquote>

<p>Cloud services work particularly well for small shops in certain situations.</p>

<p>Here are a few:
<strong></strong></p>

<ul>

<li>Youre a small shop facing increased demand for your products or services, but youre not equipped to expand your IT setup.</li>

<li>You have consistent access to secure Wi-Fi, minimizing the risks of cloud computing on the road.</li>

<li>The data youd keep in the cloud is proprietary only to your company  you dont have the added risk of liability for customers private or financial data in the event of a security breach.</li>

<li>Your business could continue operating during downtime if you lost access to the cloud for an hour  or even a day.</li>

<li>Youd benefit from the clouds scalability as your business fluctuates.</li>

<li>Youre already in the market for new software or IT services.</li>
